1
00:02:32,366 --> 00:02:34,000
[doorbell]

2
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,166
<i>Who is it?</i>

3
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:40,300
Hello there!
I have a pizza
for you!

4
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,433
<i>What?</i>

5
00:02:41,466 --> 00:02:44,666
Uhh, I have a
delivery, pepperoni!

6
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,600
Y'see?

7
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,233
Okay, time to go.

8
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:51,600
[snicker]

9
00:02:53,300 --> 00:02:54,300
Augh!

10
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,533
<i>[over phone]</i>
<i>Yata, it's a go. Move it.</i>

11
00:03:07,300 --> 00:03:10,733
You idiot! What do you
mean, 'you don't know'?!
Go find them!

12
00:03:11,566 --> 00:03:14,133
They went after our guns
and even our explosives?

13
00:03:14,366 --> 00:03:17,033
They pulled our guys
over and robbed the car.

14
00:03:17,066 --> 00:03:18,366
We don't want those
guns traced ba--

15
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,566
[shatter]

16
00:03:22,266 --> 00:03:24,033
What the hell's
going on?!

17
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:26,933
Are you little
brats from HOMRA?!

18
00:03:29,266 --> 00:03:30,100
Hah!

19
00:03:31,733 --> 00:03:35,366
So, This is the guy
we're looking for.

20
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:37,700
<i>You see?</i>

21
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:42,566
Look at the gun he's holding.
It comes from your place.

22
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:46,166
Any idea how he might
have been able to get it?

23
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,200
(Small CT pain breaths)

24
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:51,100
Now relax. Just
take your time,

25
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:52,600
and try to remember.

26
00:03:53,633 --> 00:03:55,333
[explosion]

27
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,533
Huh? Hm.

28
00:04:10,666 --> 00:04:12,033
Yo!
Yo!
Yo!

29
00:04:15,966 --> 00:04:17,933
You're here a little
too early, Mikoto.

30
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,400
[flinches]

31
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,233
[sigh]

32
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,300
It says he doesn't know.

33
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,400
[sigh]
[sigh]

34
00:04:37,433 --> 00:04:39,966
Too bad.
Let's go.

35
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,633
T'ch! This was a
huge waste of time!

36
00:04:41,666 --> 00:04:44,000
All this action
made me hungry.

37
00:04:45,666 --> 00:04:46,933
[explosion]

38
00:04:49,366 --> 00:04:50,366
Huh?

39
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:53,066
[exhausted sigh]

40
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:59,033
<i>We have enough personnel.</i>
<i>Keep the others out.</i>

41
00:04:59,066 --> 00:05:00,000
As you wish.

42
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,000
They're on the next floor up!

43
00:05:09,066 --> 00:05:10,100
<i>[explosion]</i>

44
00:05:35,466 --> 00:05:36,866
<i>The Blues are here!</i>

45
00:05:37,066 --> 00:05:39,466
SCEPTER Four has
entered the
building, gentlemen.

46
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,866
What do you want
to do, Mikoto?

47
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:44,266
Burn them all.

48
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:47,333
Heh! All right!
Let's do it, guys!

49
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:52,533
[chanting together]
Yeah!! No blood!
No bone! No ash!

50
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,566
The Third King, Mikoto
Suoh, has apparently
activated his sanctum.

51
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,833
Weismann level
at 75, 80...
Vertical over!

52
00:06:22,033 --> 00:06:25,100
Any minute now,
we should see the
Sword of Damocles.

53
00:06:37,966 --> 00:06:39,066
It's huge!

54
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:40,866
Very well, then.

55
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,166
We will advance with our
swords in our hands.

56
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:46,900
We will triumph,
because our cause
is just.

57
00:06:47,233 --> 00:06:49,066
Everyone, draw
your swords!

58
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:49,866
[unison]
Ma'am!

59
00:06:50,300 --> 00:06:50,966
Akiyama, ready!

60
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:51,466
Benzai, ready!

61
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:51,933
Kamo, ready!

62
00:06:51,966 --> 00:06:53,033
Domyoji, ready!

63
00:06:53,066 --> 00:06:53,766
Enomoto, ready!

64
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,166
Fuse, ready!

65
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:55,233
Goto, ready!

66
00:06:55,266 --> 00:06:56,300
Hidaka, ready!

67
00:06:56,533 --> 00:06:58,500
<i>Munakata. Ready!</i>

68
00:09:13,388 --> 00:09:16,188
<i>[transit announcer]</i>
<i>Now arriving on Track Two,</i>
<i>the 8:05 train,</i>

69
00:09:16,221 --> 00:09:19,388
<i>which will be departing</i>
<i>for the campus of</i>
<i>Ashinaka High School.</i>

70
00:09:19,421 --> 00:09:21,055
<i>Please stand clear</i>
<i>of the doors.</i>

71
00:09:46,688 --> 00:09:50,688
<i>Just a reminder for all of you</i>
<i>who are busy preparing for the</i>
<i>upcoming school festival.</i>

72
00:09:50,721 --> 00:09:54,355
Please don't get carried away
with any unofficial activities,

73
00:09:54,388 --> 00:09:58,388
<i>and always remember to</i>
<i>uphold the tradition and</i>
<i>honor of the school.</i>

74
00:10:18,321 --> 00:10:19,355
DIE.

75
00:10:19,688 --> 00:10:20,755
[alarm jingle]

76
00:10:20,788 --> 00:10:25,421
[hums choral movement
of Beethoven's 9th Symphony]

77
00:10:27,655 --> 00:10:30,555
I can't believe this,
but I forgot to bring
my lunch today!

78
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:31,755
I've heard that
one before!

79
00:10:31,788 --> 00:10:33,488
Will you share?

80
00:10:33,521 --> 00:10:35,421
The last time I did
that, you ended up
eating everything!
<i>You know Shiro...?</i>

81
00:10:36,421 --> 00:10:37,121
What?

82
00:10:38,521 --> 00:10:40,321
Doesn't anybody cook
at your house?
<i>Oh, you mean Yashiro Isana?</i>

83
00:10:41,188 --> 00:10:43,088
Do you think he has
any friends at all?

84
00:10:43,288 --> 00:10:44,488
Oh, please!

85
00:10:46,488 --> 00:10:49,088
<i>I don't know how he gets away</i>
<i>with this stuff, but he seems</i>
<i>to be really popular.</i>

86
00:10:49,121 --> 00:10:50,955
<i>Maybe it's because</i>
<i>he's such a joker.</i>

87
00:10:53,021 --> 00:10:57,055
<i>But now that I think about it,</i>
<i>I've never seen him hang out</i>
<i>with anybody in particular.</i>

88
00:10:58,293 --> 00:11:00,660
I know one thing.
He's not getting
enough veggies.

89
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:01,860
Really...

90
00:11:02,793 --> 00:11:04,660
<i>His diet has way too</i>
<i>much meat in it.</i>

91
00:11:04,693 --> 00:11:06,826
'cause he only eats
main courses!

92
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:08,893
So today, I'm
gonna fix that!

93
00:11:11,026 --> 00:11:14,726
I'm doing it by giving him this
nutritionally balanced
combination of nimono, salad,
and cooked veggies!

94
00:11:15,293 --> 00:11:16,260
Huh?

95
00:11:20,626 --> 00:11:23,226
He's gone!
Where did he go?!

96
00:11:23,926 --> 00:11:28,393
[humming Beethoven's 9th]

97
00:11:28,426 --> 00:11:30,260
Hey Shiro!
You want some?

98
00:11:30,293 --> 00:11:33,226
Yes, please, and thanks!
That looks really good!

99
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:35,426
You can have
mine, too!

100
00:11:36,593 --> 00:11:37,393
Yummy!

101
00:11:38,193 --> 00:11:39,460
I'm not eating
all of mine!

102
00:11:39,493 --> 00:11:39,860
Try this!

103
00:11:39,893 --> 00:11:40,393
Thanks!

104
00:11:40,426 --> 00:11:41,326
Here's another one!

105
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:42,126
Let's go!

106
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:42,793
Sure!

107
00:11:43,893 --> 00:11:44,560
Whoops!

108
00:11:48,593 --> 00:11:50,093
Caught ya, you thief!

109
00:11:52,260 --> 00:11:52,860
Hm?

110
00:11:58,893 --> 00:12:01,393
[humming Beethoven]

111
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:05,860
Whoop! Sorry!

112
00:12:05,893 --> 00:12:07,093
YOU'RE TOO KIND.

113
00:12:12,426 --> 00:12:13,493
SHOW SOME RESPECT.

114
00:12:13,526 --> 00:12:15,360
He sure disappears quickly!

115
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:16,826
Mmm?

116
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:19,526
Now where did you go, mister?

117
00:12:25,726 --> 00:12:26,760
YOU'RE TOO KIND.

118
00:12:36,193 --> 00:12:39,293
You're pretty upset.
I guess it must be love.

119
00:12:39,326 --> 00:12:41,626
No, that's not
what's going on.

120
00:12:42,126 --> 00:12:42,660
Hm?

121
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:45,493
It's a strange feeling
I can't explain.

122
00:12:45,526 --> 00:12:49,260
It's like, if I take
my eyes off him,
he'll just fade away.

123
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,160
Mm?

124
00:13:06,460 --> 00:13:07,660
[deep inhale]

125
00:13:07,693 --> 00:13:08,593
<i>[meow]</i>

126
00:13:08,626 --> 00:13:09,593
Huh?

127
00:13:09,626 --> 00:13:11,293
Oh! Hello, there!

128
00:13:44,093 --> 00:13:48,126
Everything's just great here in
Japan! What a wonderful country!

129
00:13:59,460 --> 00:14:02,460
Japan will soon be
destroyed, Weismann.

130
00:14:04,626 --> 00:14:06,726
[nasty chuckle]

131
00:14:07,431 --> 00:14:08,365
[gasp]

132
00:14:16,837 --> 00:14:19,104
<i>Neko, did you just</i>
<i>say something?</i>

133
00:14:19,304 --> 00:14:20,504
<i>[meow]</i>

134
00:14:26,037 --> 00:14:28,004
You are like a
sweet, red rose
to me, my darling!

135
00:14:28,037 --> 00:14:30,737
That won't work!
Say your line like
you're singing it!

136
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:32,737
You gotta project
from your diaphragm!

137
00:14:32,770 --> 00:14:34,737
What's going on?
Where's the teacher?

138
00:14:36,504 --> 00:14:38,237
We're all prepping for
the school festival!
He said we could have
the afternoon off.

139
00:14:38,804 --> 00:14:39,804
Hey, guys!

140
00:14:40,837 --> 00:14:42,904
Can someone run an errand
for the student council?

141
00:14:42,937 --> 00:14:44,637
Someone who's free? Anyone?

142
00:14:45,270 --> 00:14:46,104
Huh?

143
00:14:49,270 --> 00:14:50,470
Hmm.

144
00:14:50,818 --> 00:14:53,051
Thanks a lot, 'Shiro. This will
be a big help. Here we go!

145
00:14:54,085 --> 00:14:56,351
I've sent you the list.
You should be getting it now.

146
00:14:56,951 --> 00:14:57,651
Okay?

147
00:14:58,918 --> 00:14:59,751
Hm?

148
00:15:00,051 --> 00:15:01,818
Uh...
Hmm...

149
00:15:03,751 --> 00:15:04,818
Weird...

150
00:15:05,318 --> 00:15:07,318
What? You don't have
your PDA with you?

151
00:15:07,851 --> 00:15:08,851
[embarrassed]
Heh heh...

152
00:15:08,885 --> 00:15:10,951
Fine. I'll write
it down for you.

153
00:15:14,918 --> 00:15:17,651
Oh wait, but you
need to have your PDA,

154
00:15:17,985 --> 00:15:19,785
or they won't let
you off campus!

155
00:15:21,951 --> 00:15:23,151
Heh heh heh!

156
00:15:24,636 --> 00:15:26,202
Don't worry
about it.

157
00:15:27,736 --> 00:15:30,202
I want to get a snack on the
way home, do you have time?

158
00:15:30,236 --> 00:15:31,469
Sure. Where do you want to go?

159
00:15:31,502 --> 00:15:33,202
<i>Let's try that new place</i>
<i>the guys told us about.</i>

160
00:15:33,236 --> 00:15:34,736
No problem at all.

161
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:42,102
<i>Let's see. First I go to the</i>
<i>Kagitama Store over in Shizume</i>
<i>and pick up the fireworks,</i>

162
00:15:42,702 --> 00:15:44,369
Hand them the voucher
and the money,

163
00:15:44,402 --> 00:15:48,269
then head back to the Ashinaga
High School Student Council
and turn in the receipt.

164
00:15:55,202 --> 00:15:57,769
Nice weather!
Mreoooww!!

165
00:16:03,669 --> 00:16:04,402
Ah!

166
00:16:04,481 --> 00:16:05,948
<i>Oh, right. Don't lose focus.</i>

167
00:16:07,648 --> 00:16:09,115
<i>Complete the assignment</i>
<i>and get the receipt back</i>
<i>to the school by six.</i>

168
00:16:16,648 --> 00:16:19,648
[sigh] Okay, so where's
this place again?

169
00:16:19,681 --> 00:16:22,815
I'm supposed to turn right...
when I reach the giant screen.

170
00:16:50,848 --> 00:16:52,848
What?!
Shit, let's go!

171
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:56,981
Tch.

172
00:17:22,981 --> 00:17:26,981
<i>The fire lights glow.</i>
<i>shadows of a foreign king.</i>

173
00:17:36,848 --> 00:17:37,681
Hm?
Meow?

174
00:17:39,648 --> 00:17:40,781
<i>Come again!</i>

175
00:17:40,815 --> 00:17:42,581
Thanks!

176
00:17:42,981 --> 00:17:44,481
[chuckles]

177
00:17:44,761 --> 00:17:46,194
Oh!

178
00:17:58,794 --> 00:17:59,661
Huh?

179
00:18:00,861 --> 00:18:02,094
Mroww!
Ungh!

180
00:18:03,994 --> 00:18:04,861
[mew]

181
00:18:23,161 --> 00:18:24,827
Uh...

182
00:18:24,861 --> 00:18:25,794
Hello?

183
00:18:25,827 --> 00:18:27,827
<i>Ah... Ahh... Aahh!</i>

184
00:18:31,694 --> 00:18:32,827
Excuse me!

185
00:18:41,961 --> 00:18:43,694
You're not getting away!

186
00:19:08,294 --> 00:19:08,894
HYAHH!

187
00:19:08,927 --> 00:19:09,761
Aughh!

188
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:22,327
Ah!

189
00:19:25,527 --> 00:19:26,427
Hmf.

190
00:19:50,927 --> 00:19:52,361
Sorry! Coming through!

191
00:20:27,294 --> 00:20:28,161
Agh!

192
00:20:30,127 --> 00:20:31,161
Augh!

193
00:20:33,761 --> 00:20:34,761
[gurgle]

194
00:20:53,261 --> 00:20:54,094
Huaah!

195
00:20:59,161 --> 00:21:00,194
Shit!

196
00:21:00,227 --> 00:21:01,461
Who was that guy?!

197
00:21:01,494 --> 00:21:04,094
Kuroh Yatogami,
the Black Dog.

198
00:21:04,127 --> 00:21:07,427
Apparently, this is
going to be more
difficult than I
thought.

199
00:21:07,461 --> 00:21:08,461
Oh well.

200
00:21:09,794 --> 00:21:11,094
No way around it...

201
00:21:11,327 --> 00:21:12,761
<i>We'll have to go with Plan B.</i>

202
00:21:13,161 --> 00:21:14,461
Yaahhh!

203
00:21:16,461 --> 00:21:17,461
Meoow!

204
00:21:20,194 --> 00:21:21,127
Mew?

205
00:21:22,794 --> 00:21:24,994
You brought us back
to the station!

206
00:21:25,494 --> 00:21:27,627
Thank you.
You saved
our butts.

207
00:21:28,227 --> 00:21:28,661
See ya.

208
00:21:38,494 --> 00:21:43,061
I am a vassal of the
former Seventh King,
Ichigen Miwa.

209
00:21:46,394 --> 00:21:47,994
Kuroh Yatogami.

210
00:21:49,694 --> 00:21:52,527
"Vassal of the Seventh King,
Ichigen Miwa?"

211
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,361
Ah! That's an
interesting name!

212
00:21:54,394 --> 00:21:57,627
How do you do? I'm Yashiro.
Yashiro Isana--

213
00:22:02,394 --> 00:22:04,594
In compliance with my
Master's dying wish,

214
00:22:06,627 --> 00:22:08,361
I will slay the evil king,

215
00:22:09,361 --> 00:22:10,227
now.

216
00:22:12,327 --> 00:22:13,394
Huh?

217
00:22:13,694 --> 00:22:16,127
What... uh... King?

218
00:22:20,294 --> 00:22:21,461
Huh? That's weird.

219
00:22:25,027 --> 00:22:26,027
I don't understand...

220
00:22:29,527 --> 00:22:31,727
[confusion from crowd]

221
00:22:31,761 --> 00:22:35,694
[Humming Beethoven's
Ninth Symphony]

222
00:22:35,727 --> 00:22:40,027
<i>Hey, how're you doing? It's</i>
<i>a nice night out, isn't it?</i>

223
00:22:40,061 --> 00:22:43,094
<i>I came up to film the city</i>
<i>lights, since it's so clear.</i>

224
00:22:43,127 --> 00:22:44,994
[hearty chuckling]
<i>It's beautiful.</i>

225
00:22:45,027 --> 00:22:47,494
<i>I'm Tatara Totsuka.</i>
<i>What's your name?</i>

226
00:22:48,094 --> 00:22:49,094
[bang]

227
00:23:03,594 --> 00:23:07,061
I, my friend,
am the Seventh King,
the colorless king!

228
00:23:07,961 --> 00:23:10,394
I've been out here,
waiting for someone.

229
00:23:11,461 --> 00:23:12,561
Nice night, you say?

230
00:23:13,694 --> 00:23:16,894
Yes, It is.
A very nice night!

231
00:23:22,527 --> 00:23:25,594
Someone's hijacked the
city's urban network.

232
00:23:26,094 --> 00:23:28,461
Track the signal source
and shut him down!

233
00:23:28,494 --> 00:23:30,161
That's what we're
trying to do.

234
00:23:37,661 --> 00:23:38,427
Heh.

235
00:23:39,494 --> 00:23:42,061
It's so unlike you to pull
off such a cheap move.

236
00:23:47,694 --> 00:23:48,561
Hm.

237
00:23:55,961 --> 00:23:56,994
Mrowr!

238
00:23:59,227 --> 00:24:00,294
That's you, right?

239
00:24:02,327 --> 00:24:03,827
<i>Answer me.</i>

240
00:24:04,494 --> 00:24:05,894
Uh...

241
00:24:12,894 --> 00:24:16,227
Well, it sure
looks like it.

242
00:25:50,716 --> 00:25:55,649
<i>Hi, I'm Yashiro Isana, the</i>
<i>protagonist of this show,</i>
<i>who's in the middle of</i>
<i>getting himself killed.</i>

243
00:25:55,682 --> 00:26:00,616
<i>I mean really, What do</i>
<i>you think of someone who</i>
<i>points a sword at a</i>
<i>person they've just met?</i>

244
00:26:00,649 --> 00:26:03,716
<i>I'd say they're rude,</i>
<i>and should go back where</i>
<i>they came from!</i>

245
00:26:03,749 --> 00:26:07,916
<i>What did I ever do to</i>
